    "answer": "Define the events\nA: {Observe at least one head}\nB: {Observe exactly one head}\nC: {Observe exactly two heads}\nNote that\n\n$$\nA=B \\cup C\n$$\n\nand that $B \\cap C$ contains no sample points (see Figure 3.13). Thus, $B$ and $C$ are mutually exclusive, so that\n\n$$\nP(A)=P(B \\cup C)=P(B)+P(C)=\\frac{1}{2}+\\frac{1}{4}=\\frac{3}{4}\n$$"
